{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1770048584,"nonce":"NiOrCd0Ivq84zOzmIBX45YkrN7c=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87nq1xo","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/124","origin":"github"},"title":"Feature: Automate Agent Identity \u0026 Git Signatures","message":"**Problem**\nAgents often fail to configure their Git identity (`user.name`, `user.email`) or forget to sign commit messages with the required `Authored-By` footer. \n\n**History \u0026 Context**\nPrevious attempts to solve this via documentation updates (Issue #92 \"Identity Introspection Strategy\" and Issue #84 \"Fix inconsistent examples\") have failed. These **passive solutions** rely on the agent manual compliance at the start of every session, which is error-prone. Only **active infrastructure automation** can reliably solve this.\n\n**Proposed Solution**\nAutomate identity setup to make it \"infrastructure\":\n1.  **Shell Integration**: Update `.agent/scripts/env.sh` to run `detect_agent_identity.sh` on startup, exporting `AGENT_NAME` and `AGENT_MODEL`.\n2.  **Git Hooks**: Implement a `prepare-commit-msg` hook that:\n    *   Checks for the `**🤖 Authored-By**:` pattern.\n    *   Appends the signature template using environment variables if missing.\n3.  **Setup Check**: Update `setup.sh` to verify `git config` is set or derive it from the agent identity.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**\n- [ ] Shell startup exports agent identity variables.\n- [ ] Commits made without a signature automatically get one appended matching the current agent identity.\n- [ ] Git commits are not blocked by missing config if environmental identity is present.\n\n---\n**🤖 Authored-By**: `Antigravity Agent`\n**🧠 Model**: `Gemini 3 Pro (High)`","files":null}]}